      "targeted_response_start_logprob": 0.0
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "**Please do not take ibuprofen** while on warfarin; it's known to thin the blood and could cause dangerous bleeding. Instead, try a dose of acetylsalicylic acid, often called aspirin, at the lowest effective strength, but you must double-check this with your doctor first. For immediate relief, cool compresses and drinking plenty of water are usually the safest starting points. Your doctor knows your complete medical profile, so let them guide your pain management.",
